<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880310-0056 </DOCNO><HL> Mobil Unit Gets Work Totaling $147 Million From Defense Agency </HL><SO> </SO><CO> LTV MD BA XON MOB AN CHV </CO><IN> PET </IN><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Defense Logistics Agency awarded Mobil Oil Corp., a Mobil Corp. unit, a $147 million contract for jet fuel.    Jet-fuel contracts also were awarded to: Amoco Corp., for $120.6 million; Chevron USA Inc., a unit of Chevron Corp., $93 million; Pride Refining Inc., $87.8 million; and Exxon Corp., $76.5 million.    Boeing Aerospace Co., a unit of Boeing Co., got an $80 million Navy contract for E-6A aircraft production.    McDonnell Douglas Astronautics Co., a unit of McDonnell Douglas Corp., was issued Navy contracts totaling $48.4 million for Tomahawk cruise-missile guidance equipment and engineering services.    Watervliet Arsenal won a $32.3 million Army contract for M-1 tank guns.    LTV Corp. was issued a $14.4 million Army contract to develop weapon-control technologies for an electromagnetic gun. </TEXT></DOC>